    "image_with_text_YmjFkV": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_VpJWcw": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Back to Wall Toilets",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "text_n3Ehkw": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Back to wall toilets are a popular choice for modern Australian bathrooms, thanks to their clean lines and space-saving design. With the cistern either exposed and positioned directly behind the pan or built into the wall (via concealed cistern systems), these toilets sit flush against the rear wall — eliminating gaps where dust and grime typically collect.</p><p>This configuration not only enhances the visual simplicity of the space but also makes cleaning easier and more hygienic. Back to wall toilets are ideal for households that prioritise low-maintenance living, as they reduce exposed pipework and streamline the bathroom aesthetic.</p><p>In terms of functionality, they are often paired with soft-close seats, dual-flush buttons, and water-saving features — making them a practical yet stylish choice for both renovations and new builds. Whether you’re designing an urban apartment or a minimalist master suite, a back to wall toilet offers the right blend of form and function.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        },
        "button_nCzpwi": {
          "type": "button",
          "settings": {
            "button_label": "Shop Back to Wall Toilets",
            "button_link": "shopify://collections/back-to-wall-toilets"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "heading_VpJWcw",
        "text_n3Ehkw",
