    "image_with_text_dLeNVc": {
      "type": "image-with-text",
      "blocks": {
        "heading_CMMNXA": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Close Coupled Toilets",
            "heading_size": "h2"
          }
        },
        "text_n8gDHM": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Close coupled toilets feature the cistern sitting directly atop the toilet pan in one compact unit. This configuration has long been favoured in Australian homes for its traditional design, straightforward installation, and reliable performance.</p><p>While close coupled toilets may present a more conventional look than wall-hung or in-wall options, modern designs now offer cleaner silhouettes, slimline cisterns, and updated features that suit both classic and transitional bathroom styles.</p><p>They’re ideal for renovations where existing plumbing needs to be retained, or for homeowners looking for a cost-effective toilet that still delivers on performance. Many models include dual-flush buttons to support water conservation, as well as soft-close seats and ergonomic pan shapes for user comfort.</p><p>Close coupled toilets remain a practical and accessible option for families, rental properties, and multi-bathroom homes — especially where functionality and ease of maintenance are key priorities.</p>",
            "text_style": "body"
          }
        },
        "button_7XpRcQ": {
          "type": "button",
          "settings": {
            "button_label": "Shop Closed Coupled Toilets",
            "button_link": "shopify://collections/close-coupled"
          }
        }
      },
