    "collapsible_content_PJG9x7": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_ma8wfz": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What is the best type of toilet to buy for a modern bathroom?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>The best toilet for a modern bathroom depends on your space, plumbing, and aesthetic preferences. Popular choices include <strong>back to wall toilets</strong> for a sleek, minimalist look, and <strong>wall hung toilets</strong> for a floating effect that makes cleaning easier. For smart functionality, <strong>intelligent toilets</strong> offer features like heated seats, automatic flushing, and built-in bidets.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_iKBBCK": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Where can I buy high-quality toilets online in Australia?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>You can buy premium toilets online at <a href=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/toilets\">Cook & Bathe</a>, where we offer a curated range of <strong>wall hung</strong>, <strong>close coupled</strong>, <strong>back to wall toilets</strong> and <strong>smart toilets </strong>from top Australian and European brands. We deliver nationwide with trusted courier services.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_EWaYD3": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What is a rimless toilet and is it worth it?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>A <strong>rimless toilet</strong> is designed without the traditional rim inside the bowl, making it easier to clean and more hygienic. The direct flush technology improves water flow and reduces bacterial buildup. Rimless toilets are a great investment for both <strong>residential</strong> and <strong>commercial bathrooms</strong> in Australia.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_yKgqwM": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Are wall hung toilets safe and durable?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes, <strong>wall hung toilets</strong> are extremely safe and durable when installed with a quality in-wall cistern and frame system (like those from <strong>Geberit</strong> or <strong>Caroma</strong>). They’re weight-rated and engineered to support standard and above-average loads.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_aPxxTQ": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Do I need a specific cistern for a wall hung or back to wall toilet?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Yes, wall hung and some <strong>back to wall toilets</strong> require an <strong>in-wall cistern</strong>. These cisterns are concealed inside the wall cavity or within cabinetry. At Cook & Bathe, we stock compatible <strong>flush plates</strong> and <strong>concealed cisterns</strong> to match your selected toilet pan.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_XCcxcT": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What’s the most water-efficient toilet available in Australia?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Look for toilets with a <strong>WELS 4-star or 5-star rating</strong> for maximum water efficiency. Brands like <strong>Caroma</strong>, <strong>Villeroy & Boch</strong>, and <strong>Seima</strong> offer dual flush systems with average flush volumes as low as 3.5L. These options help reduce water bills and support sustainable living.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_mYVgWV": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I buy smart toilets in Australia?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>Absolutely. Smart toilets with features like bidet spray, heated seating, auto lids, and hands-free flushing are available from brands like <strong>St George</strong>. Browse our collection of <strong>smart toilets online</strong> or visit our showrooms to experience them in person.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_j6Mz9j": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "What’s the difference between a close coupled toilet and a back to wall toilet?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>A <strong>close coupled toilet</strong> has a visible cistern directly mounted on the toilet pan, making it compact and easy to install. A <strong>back to wall toilet</strong> sits flush against the wall and can have a concealed or exposed cistern. Back to wall designs provide a more streamlined appearance and are easier to clean around.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_h9tCKP": {
          "type": "collapsible_row",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Can I install a new toilet using my existing plumbing?",
            "icon": "none",
            "row_content": "<p>In many cases, yes. <strong>Close coupled toilets</strong> are ideal for using existing plumbing positions. If you’re upgrading to a <strong>wall hung</strong> or <strong>in-wall cistern system</strong>, additional plumbing modifications may be required. Speak with your installer or contact our showroom team for advice.</p>",
            "page": ""
          }
        },
        "collapsible_row_JJhpVM": {
